Cream cheese pound cake. Sharing my mom’s recipe b/c it never fails me:
3 cups sugar
3 cups cake flour 
6 eggs (add 2 at a time)
1.5 cups butter (2.5 sticks) @ room temp
1 package cream cheese @ room temp
1 teaspoon vanilla 
.50 teaspoon baking powder

Bake at 325 1.5 hrs or until you stick a toothpick into cake and it comes out clear/without batter residue 

You’re welcome 😉

This may not be the popular opinion… I don’t know I haven’t asked enough black entrepreneurs. I know y’all like to tussle, but I said it 🤷🏾‍♀️. I’m proud to be a black female entrepreneur. I appreciate people that choose to support black owned businesses. It’s strange to explain b/c I’m even a part of black owned curated shopping platforms. However, outside of that it feels like a back-handed compliment. It feels like “I’m ONLY buying b/c you’re black”. It doesn’t feel like “You have an amazing product that I want to buy and you just so happen to also be black”. Not sure if that makes sense. And let’s not talk about when a black owned business makes a customer upset. It then becomes “I only bought this b/c you’re black” or “this is why I don’t shop with black owned businesses” . It’s a slippery slope. I LOVE the support, but one can support without necessarily announcing why they support. Rant over… thanks for reading 🙃 It may resonate with some & not with others. Feel free to chime in; I WANNA KNOW!

Set up your children for success! When you know better, TEACH better!
✨If you have credit cards with excellent payment history and you keep the utilization at less than 30%, add your child as an authorized user. Don’t just get a card with their name on it… make sure the credit card company has your kid’s social security number and are reporting it to the credit bureaus. Now all your good payment history goes to your kid too! 
✨Don’t let your kid get swooned by credit card offers! As soon as they turn 18 the mail starts to come 🙄 Instead of getting an unsecured (traditional) credit card at 18, guide them to get a secured credit card. A secured credit card is a card where you/your child pays cash upfront to guarantee the credit line. Choose a card that reports to the 3 major credit bureaus; NOT ALL OF THEM REPORT!!!!OPEN SKY is a secured credit card company that reports to major credit bureaus.The limit does not need to be high. Remember the only goal is only for payments to be reported and counted towards good payment history in order to establish good credit. Open Sky allows you to open with $200. Buy gas once per month and pay it right back!
—— disclaimer—— you have to take the time to explain how credit works to your kids. Be sure that they use the card every month, even if it’s just for gas once per month. Be sure that they put a reminder in their phone when the bill is due so that they can remember to pay it. This works best with a teenager w/ an income :) 
✨ This secured card method is a good way to go if you don’t have a card that you want to add your child as an authorized user. But doing both is 🔥🔥🔥🔥

My thoughts are I want my children to graduate from college without debt (even w/ scholarship $$ there’s still expenses), want them be financial literate, have my help $ support to purchase first home, etc. Basically I want them to be set up for success. I had my family’s support throughout my endeavors. However I didn’t have it all laid out for me the way I want to do for my kids. I moved out (my choice) a few months after my 18th birthday, went to college AND worked a full time job. I worked HARD & Im still paying for these degrees🫤. My motivation to graduate & work to pay my rent, etc was that I didn’t want to go back home. People will argue that the struggle made me a “better person”. But If I can set them up, teach them to maintain/ grow $$ and encourage them to do the same for their children, why not? The goal is for each generation to do better than the previous, right?
.
I have a couple of friends that although they have the means, they don’t feel like they should contribute to their children’s college tuition- even beyond partial scholarship money. They don’t agree with buying or helping them buy a car… basically feels children should be cut off at 18. One in particular, her thoughts are that’s how her parents did it for her and she is just fine.

Which side are you on?

Yesterday goes down as one of the top three days of my life.HANDS DOWN! It was so perfect! My eldest graduated from high school and is ready to embark on his next chapter of life. We celebrated him and his achievements yesterday and it could not have been a better day. The pride, the happiness I felt and the joy I saw on his face made the day so memorable… all the feels 🥰A friend sent some words to me just a few minutes before the ceremony started. The message was so timely and should be shared with every parent this grad season:
A letter from me to you!

Dear momma

YOU DID IT. ITS ALL PLANNED. ALL SET. READY TO GO! HERE IS A MOMMA REMINDER:

On this day- graduation day- take a moment and soak it in. Take a longer look. Snap and extra picture. Inhale a little longer. Zip his robe. Place his cap. Touch his face. Say a million I love yous. Cry a little (before the makeup goes on 😆) During the ceremony- close everyone out. Tune in to him. See him rise. See him walk. See him shake hands. See him celebrate. Celebrate all you have done. And when the exit- be the first person he sees. It’s ok to leave your family- they will find you. You. Him. Live in this moment! It’s ONCE IN A LIFETIME. 

Sending you love and joy and peace today! Yes- you did it. Find the space to celebrate you! (Thanks for this @the_ceo_mom )

1. Stop reaching out to help. They will call when they need you…Even if it’s a 1:45 am b/c they can’t find the extra rolls of paper towels 🙄 true story 
2. If you check their location don’t tell them. Easiest way to break trust. Check it to ensure safety; not to question. 
3. Get more comfortable being a consultant and not the one telling them what to do anymore. 
4. If you have opted to give them spending money/allowance set an amount and when it’s gone, it’s gone! Budgeting is an essential habit!
5. Don’t call and text everyday. Give them some time to miss you. This is new to you and new to them too. They really do miss you just not the same way you miss them.
6. Relax & Trust the parenting you’ve done over the last 18 years.
7. They’re likely out enjoying their new found freedom; go do the same 🫡

Today I canceled plans & slept in. That was followed by a day of doing nothing and only returning a phone call to my son. I’ve learned that many people aren’t comfortable having solo days like this. I love them! Do you stay in and/or go out solo??
.
Learning to spend time alone is important for several reasons:

1. Self-Discovery: Alone time provides an opportunity for self-reflection and self-discovery. It allows you to better understand your thoughts, feelings, and desires without external distractions.

2. Self-Reliance: Being comfortable in your own company fosters self-reliance and independence. You learn to trust yourself and make decisions without relying on others’ input.

3. Stress Reduction: Alone time can be a stress reliever. It offers a break from the demands and pressures of social interactions, allowing you to recharge and reduce stress.

4. Creativity and Productivity: Solitude often sparks creativity and enhances productivity. It provides a conducive environment for deep thinking, problem-solving, and creative brainstorming.

5. Improved Relationships: Paradoxically, spending time alone can improve your relationships with others. It helps you develop a strong sense of self, which can lead to healthier and more fulfilling social connections.

6. Mental Well-Being: Alone time can be essential for mental well-being. It allows you to process emotions, reduce anxiety, and maintain a healthy work-life balance.

7. Personal Growth: Time alone enables personal growth and personal development. You can set goals, pursue hobbies, and work on self-improvement without external distractions.

learning to spend time alone is crucial for self-development, mental health, and building better relationships with both yourself and others.
.
#selfcare #selflove #peace

Cleaning process:
🫧 Wash sheets in hot water. In addition to detergent, Add 1 cup of Vinegar to washing machine dispenser + 1/2 cup baking soda directly to inside of washing machine drum
 🫧add equal parts vinegar + hot water to a spray bottle. Spray on mattress
🫧 sprinkle baking soda on mattress. Let sit for an hour 
🫧 steam clean mattress. The heat rids the mattress of any harmful bacteria, mold, dust mites and other allergens.

This reel is of moments from the last few weeks. It’s full of good moments & plenty of calories 😍😂none which I regret!

I finally had time this weekend to focus on what I want to achieve in 2024.

My 2024 Theme Words: EXPERIENCES & ELEVATE w/ the underlying Canceling Hustle Culture theme 

In 2024 I am buying the outfit before the special occasion arises. 

I’m buying the “good” bottle of champagne in the middle of the week. I’m not waiting for a celebration. Everyday deserves a celebration 🎉 🍾 

I’m pulling out the nice plates for dinner (even if I’m solo) and not waiting to use them for a dinner party or a holiday. 

I’m drinking my morning coffee from a beautiful mug that I love and stirring it with a fancy spoon. 

I’m buying the sheets with higher thread count because I like the way it feels on my skin… not just b/c I need new sheets. 

I’m elevating the sweatpants and tshirt I wear to the run errands. No more walking out the house looking like a bum even if I’m just going to the gas station! 

I’m buying the ingredients to recreate my favorite cocktails at my house while sitting on furniture that I love. B/c I should be able to eat or drink what I love whenever I want in a room that brings me peace & comfort. 

I’m buying the $$$ candle that I loved at my favorite hotel b/c I shouldn’t have to wait for a vacation to experience a scent that makes me happy. 

I’m removing things that don’t bring me JOY. Everyday should be filled with my favorite experience - big or small. 

Why? Because I deserve it…All of it. We all do!

As opposed to focusing on financial & professional goals, my focus is on how I want to FEEL. Sometimes it’s not always THINGS or achievements that we want; sometimes it’s just the feeling that it brings which we really desire. Focus on the feelings and you will naturally manifest the extra money, success, things etc ❤️ it will be drawn to you. 

What’s your theme or your word for 2024?
